{{unreferenced|date=August 2016}} {{Infobox Book | name = I Don't Mean to be Rude, but...: The Truth about Fame, Fortune and My Life in Music | title_orig = | translator = | image = I Don't Mean to be Rude, but....jpg | image_caption = | author = Simon Cowell | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = England | language = English | series = | subject = [[Simon Cowell]] and [[Idol series]] | genre = [[Autobiography]] | publisher = Ebury Press | release_date = 29 April 2004 | english_release_date = | media_type = | pages = 256 | isbn = 0-09-189828-5 | oclc= 56457537 | preceded_by = | followed_by = [[I Don't Mean to Be Rude, But...: Backstage Gossip from American Idol & the Secrets that Can Make You a Star]] }} '''''I Don't Mean to be Rude, but...''''' is a 2003 autobiographical book by the television personality and music critic [[Simon Cowell]]. The book gives an insight into [[Simon Cowell]]'s life as well as backstage gossip and tips on how to be successful.
