'''Puppet Animation Scotland''' is [[Scotland]]'s national organisation for the promotion and development of [[puppetry]] and [[animation]] as art forms.

They have three annual festivals:
* Puppet Animation Festival. This is Scotland largest and longest established performing arts event for children and their families.{{Citation needed|date=May 2011}} Every Easter, puppetry companies tour their shows around Scotland to all sorts of venues from large city centre theatres to small village halls.
* ''manipulate'' Visual Theatre Festival. manipulate is a festival of innovative theatre arts presented by Puppet Animation Scotland at the [http://www.traverse.co.uk Traverse Theatre] in Edinburgh.
* Animated Islands. This festival is currently in development for Autumn 2011.

Puppet Animation Scotland’s portfolio of festivals and support schemes provide the means to foster creativity, innovation and excellence throughout Scotland’s professional puppetry and animation communities.{{Citation needed|date=May 2011}} Puppet Animation Scotland also offers a range of skills development opportunities for young practitioners preparing for entry into the sector. This portfolio  of professional opportunity and skills development has supported Scottish puppeteers in presenting their work to more than 1.4million people throughout the UK.{{Citation needed|date=May 2011}}

Puppet Animation Scotland is supported by [http://www.creativescotland.co.uk Creative Scotland].

